04/04/2004
OHRID, Macedonia -- The Macedonian and Swiss defence ministries agreed Saturday (3 April) to set up a regional public relations training centre. 
Among other activities, the centre will release joint video productions from countries in Southeast Europe, including Macedonia's Adriatic Charter partners, Albania and Croatia. 
Switzerland will allocate 200,000 euros for the project, in addition to providing technical equipment and instructors. 
Training is to begin in a year.
In other news, Macedonian Finance Minister Nikola Popovski and World Bank Manager for Macedonia Sandrar Bloemenkamp signed a $5m loan agreement Friday to fund an education modernisation project in Macedonia. 
(MIA - 03/04/04; MIA - 02/04/04)
